Article.ArticleTitle: Reply to the 'Comment on "Atmospheric chemistry of iodine anions: elementary reactions of I<sup>-</sup>, IO<sup>-</sup>, and IO with ozone studied in the gas-phase at 300 K using an ion trap"' by D. Britz, Phys. Chem. Chem. Phys., 2019, 21, C9CP03851E.

AbstractText: We reply to the comment by Dieter Britz on two recent papers in Physical Chemistry Chemical Physics. The comment presents a valuable, however, less flexible, alternative to the analysis performed in these papers and as such has no impact on any of the scientific results reported in the two publications.
